create_records.import.bullet1.defaultMessage: Use the “Download Template” button to download a template for this deployment.

create_records.import.bullet2.defaultMessage: Create the CSV you’d like to upload, so that it matches the template provided. It must be a comma “,” delimited file and we do not currently support semicolon delimited “;” files. Column order does not matter but properly named headers are required and any lines of data missing a User ID “uuid” will be omitted. Any fields containing a comma must be quote wrapped.

create_records.import.bullet3.defaultMessage: To set consent field values, use a value of 1, 0, true or false. If no value is provided no changes will be made to the consent field for that record.

create_records.import.bullet4.defaultMessage: Upload the CSV you created using the “Add from CSV” button.

create_records.import.bullet5.defaultMessage: Review the data preview to ensure the file is properly formatted and the data displays correctly in the preview. If revisions are needed click the “Cancel” button and repeat the process.

create_records.import.bullet6.defaultMessage: Click the “Import” button to import all records in the uploaded file. Please note that this action is permanent and cannot be undone.
